See Also:
getLabel(String, Locale)

getLabel

public String getLabel(String key,
                       Locale locale)

Get the label for the key in the specified Locale. The following process is used (in sequence) to get the label for the key.

  1. An explict label defined in setLabels(Map)
  2. The label for the propetry name portion of a sub key (e.g. For the key "organization.name" the property name portion is "organization", so the label would be the label for the key "organization").
  3. The label for the link text key of a link key (e.g. For the key "Link(view, id)" the link text key is "id", so the label would be the label for the key "id"
  4. The key converted to Upper Case Words.

After the first call for a particular key the calculated labels are cached.

Parameters:
key - The key.
locale - The locale.
Returns:
The label.
